name: $deleteCache
description: This function will delete the cache with the given name
example:
$createCache[test]
$deleteCache[test] // deletes the cache with the name test

$deleteCache[test2] // returns error, cache not found

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache to delete

name: $createCache
description: This function will create a new cache with the given name
example:
$createCache[test] // creates a new cache with the name test
$createCache[test2] // creates a new cache with the name test2

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache to create

name: $cacheDataSize
description: This function returns the size of the cache data
example:
$createCache[test]
$setCacheData[test;key;value]
$cacheDataSize[test]  // returns 1

$cacheDataSize[test2] // returns error, cache not found

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache data to get the size of

name: $deleteCacheData
description: This function will delete the cache data with the given name and key
example:
$createCache[test]
$setCacheData[test;key;value]
$deleteCacheData[test;key] // deletes the cache data with the name test and key key

$deleteCacheData[test;key2] // returns error, cache data not found

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache

params.name: key
params.description: The key of the cache data to delete

name: $getCacheData
description: This function will return the cache data with the given name and key
example:
$createCache[test]
$setCacheData[test;key;value]
$getCacheData[test;key] // returns value

$getCacheData[test;key2] // returns nothing

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache

params.name: key
params.description: The key of the cache data to get

name: $hasCache
description: This function will return true if the cache with the given name exists
example:
$createCache[test]
$hasCache[test] // returns true
$hasCache[test2] // returns false

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache to check

name: $setCacheData
description: This function will set the cache data with the given name and key

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache

params.name: key
params.description: The key of the cache data to set

params.name: value
params.description: The value of the cache data to set

name: $hasCacheData
description: This function will return true if the cache data with the given name and key exists
example:
$createCache[test]
$setCacheData[test;key;value]
$hasCacheData[test;key] // returns true

$hasCacheData[test;key2] // returns false

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the cache

params.name: key
params.description: The key of the cache data to check

name: $let
description: This will store temporary variables which can be retrieved by $get
example:
$let[varname;value] // Stores a temporary variable with the name 'varname' and the value 'value'
$get[varname] // Returns the value of the temporary variable with the name 'varname'

params.name: varname
params.description: Name of the temporary variable

params.name: value
params.description: Value of the temporary variable you want to save

name: $const
description: This function will store constant temporary variables which can be retrieved by $get
example:
$const[varname;value] // Stores a constant temporary variable with the name 'varname' and the value 'value'
$let[varname;value] // return error, because varname is already a constant variable

$get[varname] // Returns the value of the constant temporary variable with the name 'varname'

params.name: varname
params.description: Name of the temporary variable

params.name: value
params.description: Value of the temporary variable you want to save

name: $get
description: This will retrieve temporary variables stored ny $let or $const
example:
$let[varname;value] // Stores a temporary variable with the name 'varname' and the value 'value'
$get[varname] // Returns the value of the temporary variable with the name 'varname'

params.name: varname
params.description: Temporary variable you want to retrieve

name: $title

$title[Title;https://example.com;2] // sets the title of the second embed

params.name: title
params.description: The title for the embed

params.name: url
params.description: The URL for the title

params.name: index
params.description: The index to add this data to

name: $addField
description: This function will add a field to the embed
example:

$addField[Title;Content;true;2] // adds the field to the second embed

$addField[;Content;true] // adds the field with a blank title

params.name: title
params.description: The field title for the embed

params.name: content
params.description: The field content for the embed

params.name: inline
params.description: Whether the field should be inline

params.name: index
params.description: The index to add this data to

name: $description

params.name: index

name: $channelSendMessage

example:

params.name: returnId

example:

params.description: Whether to return the error status of the execution

description: This function will suppress errors and not send them to the channel the command was sent in.

params.name: message

params.name: input
